{"review": [{"text_id": "SJl8R-eTnQ", "sid": 0, "sentence": "The paper proposes an approach to adapt hyperparameters online."}, {"text_id": "SJl8R-eTnQ", "sid": 1, "sentence": "When learning rates are in focus, a convincing message would be to show that adaptation of learning rates is more efficient and simpler than their scheduling when tested on state-of-the-art architectures."}, {"text_id": "SJl8R-eTnQ", "sid": 2, "sentence": "A. You demonstrate the results on CIFAR-10 for 10% error rates which corresponds to networks which are far from what is currently used in deep learning."}, {"text_id": "SJl8R-eTnQ", "sid": 3, "sentence": "Thus, it is hard to say whether the results are applicable in practice."}, {"text_id": "SJl8R-eTnQ", "sid": 4, "sentence": "B. You don't schedule learning rates for your baseline methods except for a single experiment for some initial learning rate."}, {"text_id": "SJl8R-eTnQ", "sid": 5, "sentence": "C. Your method involves a hyperparameter to be tuned which affects the shape of the schedule."}, {"text_id": "SJl8R-eTnQ", "sid": 6, "sentence": "This hyperparameter itself benefits from (requires?) some scheduling."}, {"text_id": "SJl8R-eTnQ", "sid": 7, "sentence": "It would be interesting to see if the proposed method is competitive for training contemporary networks and w.r.t. simple schedule schemes."}, {"text_id": "SJl8R-eTnQ", "sid": 8, "sentence": "Online tuning of  hyperparameters is an important functionality and I hope your paper will make it more straightforward to use it in practice."}, {"text_id": "SJl8R-eTnQ", "sid": 9, "sentence": "* Minor notes:"}, {"text_id": "SJl8R-eTnQ", "sid": 10, "sentence": "You mention that \"APO converges quickly from different starting points on the Rosenbrock surface\" but 10000 iterations is not quick at all for the 2-dimensional Rosenbrock, it is extremely slow compared to 100-200 function evaluations needed for Nelder-Mead to solve it. I guess you mean"}, {"text_id": "SJl8R-eTnQ", "sid": 11, "sentence": "w.r.t. the original RMSprop."}], "reviewlabels": [{"text_id": "SJl8R-eTnQ", "sid": 0, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Summary", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "SJl8R-eTnQ", "sid": 1, "labels": {"coarse": "Evaluative", "fine": "Evaluative", "asp": "Substance", "pol": "N-Negative"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "SJl8R-eTnQ", "sid": 2, "labels": {"coarse": "Evaluative", "fine": "Evaluative", "asp": "Substance", "pol": "N-Negative"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "SJl8R-eTnQ", "sid": 3, "labels": {"coarse": "Evaluative", "fine": "Evaluative", "asp": "Substance", "pol": "N-Negative"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "SJl8R-eTnQ", "sid": 4, "labels": {"coarse": "Evaluative", "fine": "Evaluative", "asp": "Soundness/Correctness", "pol": "N-Negative"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "SJl8R-eTnQ", "sid": 5, "labels": {"coarse": "Evaluative", "fine": "Evaluative", "asp": "Soundness/Correctness", "pol": "N-Negative"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "SJl8R-eTnQ", "sid": 6, "labels": {"coarse": "Evaluative", "fine": "Evaluative", "asp": "Soundness/Correctness", "pol": "N-Negative"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "SJl8R-eTnQ", "sid": 7, "labels": {"coarse": "Request", "fine": "Request.Experiment", "asp": "Substance", "pol": "N-Negative"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "SJl8R-eTnQ", "sid": 8, "labels": {"coarse": "Other", "fine": "Other", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "SJl8R-eTnQ", "sid": 9, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Heading", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "SJl8R-eTnQ", "sid": 10, "labels": {"coarse": "Other", "fine": "Other", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": true}, {"text_id": "SJl8R-eTnQ", "sid": 11, "labels": {"coarse": "Other", "fine": "Other", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": true}], "rebuttal": [{"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 0, "sentence": "Thank you for your helpful comments."}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 1, "sentence": "We have addressed your concern about the baseline models and learning rate schedules in our updated paper."}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 2, "sentence": "Q: It is hard to say whether the results are applicable in practice; need updates to baselines and comparison with learning rate schedules."}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 3, "sentence": "We have updated the baselines in our paper for CIFAR-10 and CIFAR-100, using a larger, modern network, ResNet34, in place of the VGG11 model used previously."}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 4, "sentence": "We also compared APO to manual learning rate decay schedules."}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 5, "sentence": "For CIFAR-10/100, we trained for 200 epochs, decaying the learning rate by a factor of 5 three times during training."}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 6, "sentence": "The ResNet34 with a custom learning rate decay schedule achieves 93-94% test accuracy on CIFAR-10 and ~74% test accuracy on CIFAR-100."}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 7, "sentence": "We believe that this is a strong baseline, and shows the applicability of APO in practical settings."}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 8, "sentence": "The final test accuracies of the updated model using SGD/SGDm with and without APO are:"}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 9, "sentence": "| CIFAR-10 | CIFAR-100 |"}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 10, "sentence": "--------------------------+--------------+---------------+"}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 11, "sentence": "SGD (fixed lr)"}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 12, "sentence": "92.97            72.69"}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 13, "sentence": "SGDm (fixed lr)"}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 14, "sentence": "92.77            72.53"}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 15, "sentence": "SGD (decayed lr)"}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 16, "sentence": "93.29            73.45"}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 17, "sentence": "SGDm (decayed lr)"}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 18, "sentence": "93.53            73.80"}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 19, "sentence": "SGD-APO"}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 20, "sentence": "93.82            74.65"}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 21, "sentence": "SGDm-APO"}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 22, "sentence": "94.59            73.89"}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 23, "sentence": "The test accuracies using RMSprop and K-FAC with APO are shown in our response to all reviewers at the top."}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 24, "sentence": "The results in these tables show that APO is competitive with manual schedules in terms of test accuracy."}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 25, "sentence": "The updated figures in our paper show that APO is competitive with manual schedules both in terms of test accuracy and training loss."}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 26, "sentence": "Q: Does the hyperparameter lambda itself benefit from some scheduling?"}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 27, "sentence": "In our updated paper we show that APO with a fixed lambda achieves comparable performance to manual learning rate decay schedules."}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 28, "sentence": "While using a schedule for lambda can potentially further improve performance, a simple grid search over fixed lambda values already leads to strong performance, and has the advantage that it is easy to use in practice."}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 29, "sentence": "Q: You mention that \"APO converges quickly from different starting points on the Rosenbrock surface\" but 10000 iterations is not quick at all for the 2-dimensional Rosenbrock, it is extremely slow compared to 100-200 function evaluations needed for Nelder-Mead to solve it."}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 30, "sentence": "I guess you mean"}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 31, "sentence": "w.r.t. the original RMSprop."}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 32, "sentence": "Yes, we intended to say that on Rosenbrock, RMSprop-APO converges quickly compared to baseline RMSprop; we have updated the paper to clarify this."}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 33, "sentence": "Thank you for your helpful feedback. We have incorporated your suggestions into the updated paper."}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 34, "sentence": "Specifically, we have:"}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 35, "sentence": "* Updated the baseline model for CIFAR-10/100 from VGG11 to ResNet34."}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 36, "sentence": "* Used manual learning rate decay schedules for the CIFAR-10/100 baselines."}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 37, "sentence": "We obtained 93-94% test accuracy on CIFAR-10 (SGD/SGDm/RMSprop/K-FAC) and 73-74% test accuracy on CIFAR-100 (SGD/SGDm)."}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 38, "sentence": "All are compared to their APO variants, which performed as well or better."}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 39, "sentence": "The final results are shown in the table in the response to all reviewers at the top."}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 40, "sentence": "* Shown that APO is competitive with manual schedules both in terms of test accuracy and training loss with ResNet34."}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 41, "sentence": "This demonstrates the practical applicability of APO for contemporary networks."}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 42, "sentence": "* Updated Figure 2 on CIFAR-10 with SGD/SGDm/RMSprop, Figure 4 on CIFAR-100 with SGD/SGDm, and Figure 6 on CIFAR-10 with SGD."}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 43, "sentence": "We also added Figure 3 on CIFAR-10 with K-FAC."}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 44, "sentence": "Each figure compares the baseline optimizers with their APO variants."}, {"text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 45, "sentence": "Thank you for having helped us improve the paper."}], "rebuttallabels": [{"labels": {"alignments": [], "responsetype": "social", "coarseresponse": "nonarg"}, "text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 0}, {"labels": {"alignments": [4], "responsetype": "done_manu_Yes", "coarseresponse": "concur"}, "text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 1}, {"labels": {"alignments": [2, 3], "responsetype": "structuring", "coarseresponse": "nonarg"}, "text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 2}, {"labels": {"alignments": [2, 3], "responsetype": "done_manu_Yes", "coarseresponse": "concur"}, "text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 3}, {"labels": {"alignments": [2, 3], "responsetype": "done_manu_Yes", "coarseresponse": "concur"}, "text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 4}, {"labels": {"alignments": [2, 3], "responsetype": "done_manu_Yes", "coarseresponse": "concur"}, "text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 5}, {"labels": {"alignments": [2, 3], "responsetype": "done_manu_Yes", "coarseresponse": "concur"}, "text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 6}, {"labels": {"alignments": [2, 3], "responsetype": "done_manu_Yes", "coarseresponse": "concur"}, "text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 7}, {"labels": {"alignments": [2, 3], "responsetype": "done_manu_Yes", "coarseresponse": "concur"}, "text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 8}, {"labels": {"alignments": [2, 3], "responsetype": "done_manu_Yes", "coarseresponse": "concur"}, "text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 9}, {"labels": {"alignments": [2, 3], "responsetype": "structuring", "coarseresponse": "nonarg"}, "text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 10}, {"labels": {"alignments": [2, 3], "responsetype": "done_manu_Yes", "coarseresponse": "concur"}, "text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 11}, {"labels": {"alignments": [2, 3], "responsetype": "done_manu_Yes", "coarseresponse": "concur"}, "text_id": "Bkld8r3FRQ", "sid": 12}, {"labels": {"alignments": [2, 3], "responsetype": "done_manu_Yes", "coarseresponse